Package org.assistments.livechart.affectdetector.affectextractor

Class FeatureDistiller3

java.lang.Object
org.assistments.livechart.affectdetector.affectextractor.FeatureDistiller3
public class FeatureDistiller3 extends Object
This class will add all the features to my P(T) data sets. Many methods could be combined together to increase the efficiency of distilling these features, but I sacrificed that in favor of understandability and separation of each feature into its own method.
Author:
abg

    • printToFile

      public void printToFile​(BufferedWriter writer)
      Prints out a new file with the old data set info and our current new features. Only the aggregate rows will be included, not one row for each action. I ran into memory issues trying to load everything at once, so this will be called after each method to load in the new features as we distill them. This is a waste of time but seems to be the only way to pull it off with given memory.

    • addAfrUsedHintSuccessfully

      public void addAfrUsedHintSuccessfully()
      This method checks to see, if the current action is correct, if the previous action was a hint. The previous action must be on the same problem and it cannot be a bottom out hint. Obviously, this can only happen once after first response, so this is a binary feature.

      public void addAfrAttemptCount()

      public void addAfrWrongCount()
      This method counts the number of wrong answers the user submitted on this problem. Help attempts don't count; The count is only for pure answer attempts that were incorrect

    • addTotalFrAttempted

      public void addTotalFrAttempted()
      This method adds up the total number of problems the user has ever attempted. This hopefully will be a rough idea of user familiarity with the system. We maintain a hash of users to a set of all problems they have seen. The set will keep the seen problems unique and we can just take the size of it to know how many individual problems they have attempted
